OIL CONTAMINATION, WILDLIFE - USA: (GULF COAST, MICHIGAN) CLEANUP
****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this posting:
[1] Gulf Coast
[2] Michigan (Kalamazoo River)

******
[1] Gulf Coast
Date: Wed 28 Jul 2010
Source: YubaNet.com, Louisiana Bucket Brigade report [edited]
<http://yubanet.com/usa/Despite-Reports-of-Contaminated-Wildlife-States-Reopening-Waters-to-Fishing.php?>


Dead fish mixed with tar balls wash up along the beaches in Pensacola,
Florida. Laughing gulls fall from the sky along the Mississippi River
in Empire, Louisiana. A posted photo shows a small hammerhead shark
lying on a beach near Gulf Shores, Alabama, streaked with oil.

In the last week [21-28 Jul 2010], Gulf Coast residents continued to
post findings of injured and dead wildlife washed ashore, even as
Louisiana reopened certain waters to sports fishing and Alabama
reopened parts of Mobile Bay to shrimping.

"Laughing gulls on 3 separate occasions have been spotted on LA 23
falling from the sky dead," read the report out of Empire, La.

View the Oil Spill Crisis Map at <http://labucketbrigade.org>.

