- Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

[The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has done numerous tests on the
fish, shrimp and other food sources from the gulf. Multitudes of tests
have proven the marine food source to be safe for human consumption.

There is a difference in the edible marine life being safe for
consumption and the [safety of] birds and marine mammals coming up or
landing in the heavy crude oil that may be in the area.

The Michigan spill is much more recent than the gulf spill, and the
layer of oil does not have quite the ability to disperse in a short
time.

Oil can be toxic to humans and animals and proper training for
cleaning the animals is necessary for appropriate handling of the
animals and protection of each worker. - Mod.TG]

[Photo of oil-coated seabird:
<http://enviroterrorist.files.wordpress.com/2008/07/bird-oil.jpg>
- Mod.JW]
